The paper discusses a novel architecture for deep learning using recurrent sub-networks of spiking Random Neural Networks (RNN) with dense soma-to-soma interactions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of this architecture for learning from multi-channel datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of images as input data, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of sensor-based data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
